       <header>
        <h1 class="entry-title"><a href="/cms/406/USRP/GNU.Radio.Companion">Software Radio Examples</a></h1>
        <p class="meta">
         <time datetime="2011-07-15 08:55:04+01:00" pubdate data-updated="true">July 15, 2011</time>
        </p>
       </header>

       <div class="entry-content">
        <p>I did a video demonstrating the Ettus Research N210 Universal Software Radio Peripheral and several open-source software projects. In particular, we looked at OpenBTS which allows you to create an extremely cost effective cellular phone service and GNU Radio Companion which lets you upload programs in the form of flow graphs to emulate a wide variety of radio systems.<br /><br /><object width="425" height="350"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/pTb1_v8M6iA"></param><param name="wmode" value="transparent"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/pTb1_v8M6iA" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" width="425" height="350"></embed></object><br /><br />As the N210 is of a newer variety than the much more common legacy USB USRP devices, many of the GNU Radio Companion examples don't work because they implement the UHD radio interface. I've gone through a number of the examples and converted them to work with the UHD devices.<br /><br /><a href="http://anders.com/1offs/grc/am_rx_uhd.grc">http://anders.com/1offs/grc/am_rx_uhd.grc</a> - AM Receiver<br /><a href="http://anders.com/1offs/grc/wfm_rx_uhd.grc">http://anders.com/1offs/grc/wfm_rx_uhd.grc</a> - Mono FM Receiver<br /><a href="http://anders.com/1offs/grc/fm_rx_uhd.grc">http://anders.com/1offs/grc/fm_rx_uhd.grc</a> - Stereo FM Receiver<br /><br />OZ9AEC has some <a href="http://www.oz9aec.net/index.php/gnu-radio/grc-examples">interesting (very similar) examples</a> as well.</p>
       </div>

       <footer>
        <p class="meta">
         <span class="byline author vcard">Posted by <span class="fn"><a rel="author" href="http://andersbrownworth.com/">Anders Brownworth</a></span></span>
